nic data with no need to introduce a low-energy break in the\nproton and helium spectra, as it would be required for high reacceleration\nmodels. We also compare our models with the preliminary $e^-$ and $e^+$\nabsolute spectra recently measured by AMS-02. We find that those data,\ndifferently from what is inferred from the positron fraction alone, favor a\nhigh energy cutoff (about 10 TeV) of the extra component if this is uniquely\ngenerated in the Galactic arms. A lower cutoff may be allowed if a relevant\ncontribution from powerful $e^-$ + $e^+$ nearby accelerators is invoked.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 21 Nov 2013 21:03:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 3 Mar 2014 15:09:03 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 14 Apr 2014 08:43:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-04-30"}
