 least one article. Most observations were used more than once,\nyielding on average a factor of two in usage on available observing time per\nyear. About 20% of all slew observations have been used in publications. The\nscientific productivity of XMM-Newton remains extremely high with no evidence\nthat it is decreasing after more than 13 years of operations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 22 Nov 2013 13:54:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 28 Nov 2013 08:45:13 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 15 Jan 2014 09:16:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-18"}
